{"parse":{"title":"Nicholas Chare","pageid":39771357,"revid":829323017,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Nicholas Chare</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Residence</th><td class=\"label\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Australia\" title=\"Australia\">Australia</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Known&#160;for</th><td>\n<i>Auschwitz and Afterimages: Abjection, Witnessing and Representation</i> (2011)<br /><i>After Francis Bacon: Synaesthesia and Sex in Paint</i> (2012)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Awards</th><td>\n2007 <a href=\"/wiki/Philip_Leverhulme_Prize\" title=\"Philip Leverhulme Prize\">Leverhulme Trust Award</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-leverhulme_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-leverhulme-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b>Scientific career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Fields</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Gender_studies\" title=\"Gender studies\">Gender studies</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Melbourne\" title=\"University of Melbourne\">University of Melbourne</a></td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.culture-communication.unimelb.edu.au/study/gender_studies/nicholas-chare\">Profile</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Nicholas Chare</b> is a professor of <a href=\"/wiki/Art_history\" title=\"Art history\">art history</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/Universit%C3%A9_de_Montr%C3%A9al\" title=\"Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al\">Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al</a>. He received his <a href=\"/wiki/Bachelor_of_Arts\" title=\"Bachelor of Arts\">Bachelor of Arts</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/English_studies\" title=\"English studies\">English</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_art\" title=\"History of art\">history of art</a> from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Leeds\" title=\"University of Leeds\">University of Leeds</a> in 1997, and his <a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_Arts\" title=\"Master of Arts\">Master of Arts</a> in the social history of art from the same institution in 1998.<sup id=\"cite_ref-profile_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-profile-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He received his <a href=\"/wiki/PhD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PhD\">PhD</a> from the University of Leeds in 2005.<sup id=\"cite_ref-profile_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-profile-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He has served as an instructor at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Melbourne\" title=\"University of Melbourne\">University of Melbourne</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-mcmanus_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-mcmanus-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> the University of Leeds, the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Reading\" title=\"University of Reading\">University of Reading</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_York\" title=\"University of York\">University of York</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Goldsmiths,_University_of_London\" title=\"Goldsmiths, University of London\">Goldsmiths, University of London</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-profile_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-profile-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He is the author of <i>Auschwitz and Afterimages: Abjection, Witnessing and Representation</i>, <i>After Francis Bacon: Synaesthesia and Sex in Paint</i> and co-editor of <i>Representing Auschwitz: At the Margins of Testimony</i> (2013).\n</p><p>Chare was a 2007 recipient of the <a href=\"/wiki/Philip_Leverhulme_Prize\" title=\"Philip Leverhulme Prize\">Leverhulme Trust Award</a> recognising his research into paintings by <a href=\"/wiki/Francis_Bacon_(artist)\" title=\"Francis Bacon (artist)\">Francis Bacon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-leverhulme_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-leverhulme-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Works</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Books\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Books</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nicholas_Chare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nicholas_Chare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Chare, Nicholas (2011). <i>Auschwitz and Afterimages: Abjection, Witnessing and Representation</i>. London: I.B. Tauris. <a href=\"/wiki/OCLC\" title=\"OCLC\">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/oclc/663446345\">663446345</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2